cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses resource provisioning and scheduling in data centers and cloud environments, which falls under the scope of distributed and cluster computing. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper briefly mentions the allocation of resources based on first-come, first-served basis, which is related to network and internet architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of Local Resource Management Systems (LRMS) and cloud schedulers for efficient resource allocation, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the limitations of current cloud schedulers and proposes improvements, which can be seen as a software engineering problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper briefly mentions the static partitioning of resources, which can be seen as a programming language issue related to resource allocation.
